# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Sentiment Radar — Environment Variables
#
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS:
#   1. Copy this file:  copy .env.example .env   (in your project folder)
#   2. Fill in values below
#   3. Save — app reads .env automatically on startup
#   NEVER commit .env to GitHub (it is in .gitignore)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────


# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# YOUTUBE API KEY — optional, enables YouTube tab
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# How to get (free, 5 minutes, no billing needed):
#   1. Go to https://console.cloud.google.com
#   2. Sign in with any Google account
#   3. Click "Select a project" (top bar) → "New Project"
#      Name: SentimentRadar → Create
#   4. In search bar type: YouTube Data API v3 → click Enable
#   5. Left sidebar → Credentials → Create Credentials → API Key
#   6. Copy the key shown (starts with AIzaSy...)
#   Quota: 10,000 units/day = ~200 topic searches/day (free)
#
YOUTUBE_API_KEY=


# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# REDDIT CREDENTIALS — optional, improves Reddit results
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# WITHOUT these: app uses Pullpush.io archive (still works, no key needed)
# WITH these: app uses official Reddit API (faster, more fresh data)
#
# How to get (free):
#   1. Go to https://www.reddit.com/prefs/apps
#   2. Scroll down → "Create App" / "Create Another App"
#   3. Name: SentimentRadar | Type: script | Redirect URI: http://localhost:8080
#   4. Complete reCAPTCHA → Create app
#   5. Under app name = Client ID | "secret" field = Client Secret
#
REDDIT_CLIENT_ID=
REDDIT_CLIENT_SECRET=
REDDIT_USER_AGENT=SentimentRadar/1.0


# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# NO KEY NEEDED FOR:
# ══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# HackerNews — works automatically
# Dev.to     — works automatically
# Reddit     — works via Pullpush fallback even without credentials
# Bluesky    — works automatically (enable toggle in sidebar)
